other_tests.findings: The appendix appears dilated throughout its course, measuring up to 12 mm in maximum diameter, with a thickened wall and filled with fluid. There is periappendiceal mesenteric stranding, but no evidence of microperforation or focal fluid collection. The base of the cecum shows an edematous thickened wall adjacent to the ostium of the appendix. The intra-abdominal loops of small and large bowel are otherwise unremarkable without evidence of wall thickening or obstruction. There is no free air or ascites. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes are identified.
